/static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1860536835/image_1860536835.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"></picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-credits\">The Good Brigade</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p>Back in August, I <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4710575-alphatec-creating-some-real-back-pain-for-its-shareholders\">believed</a> that <strong>Alphatec (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ATEC\" title=\"Alphatec Holdings, Inc.\">ATEC</a></span>)</strong> was creating real back pains for its investors. Continued losses, incurred dilution and a focus on growth over margins made investors very cautious.</p> <p>Despite topline growth and low sales</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1860536835/image_1860536835.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4741781-alphatec-big-recovery", "pub_date": "2024-12-03 19:33:43"}, {"id": "4741780", "title": "USRT: Large Cap U.S. REITs Likely To Trail Small Peers In 2025", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/901883272/image_901883272.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Real Estate concept\" data-id=\"901883272\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"865px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/901883272/image_901883272.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/901883272/image_901883272.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/901883272/image_901883272.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/901883272/image_901883272.jpg?io=getty-